Lactantius Firmianus speaking of the end of the world, saith: Si erunt boni,
Lactant. Acephali c. 11 praede ac ludibrio habebuntur. If there remaine any good men at that time, they shall be cou • ted a pray, a booty, a mocking stocke. Canst thou not flatter? Canst thou not lye? Canst thou not play the Hyppocrite? Canst thou not follow the fashion, and serue the stage? No, then thou art no méete man to liue in this world: choose a few companions. But I say vnto you as Nestor did vnto his children;
pray, for vnlesse God helpe vs, wee all perish.
